cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO 

This paper is about object detection using a convolutional neural network, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the architecture of the network and how it can be used to improve the accuracy of other deep learning networks, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of transfer learning is also mentioned, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the network in robotics (cs.RO) for object detection and localization.
